## 6. Pros & Cons

* **Pros:**
    * Incredible balance between an aggressive tensor engine and short-game control.
    * Very high safety margin (throw angle) for opening loops against backspin.
    * Highly predictable and linear feedback, making it easy to master.
* **Cons:**
    * Lacks the absolute brutal finishing speed of 50+ degree rubbers (like Omega VII Tour or MX-K).
    * Because it is so balanced, extreme specialist players (pure smashers or pure flat-hitters) might find it lacks a distinct "extreme" characteristic.

